[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 2/100 path 6/8 answer='Tom\'s trip is divided into two parts: going and returning.\n\nFor the first part (from 1 to 4 PM), he sails at 10 miles per hour. Since there is no specific distance given for his journey, we\'ll assume that "going" refers to the entire 3-hour period between 1 PM and 4 PM. Therefore:\n\nTime taken to go = Total time - Return time\n                    = 3 hours - 1 hour\n                    = 2 hours\n\nNow, for the return trip:\n\nRate = 10 mph\nDistance = Rate × Time = 10 mph × 1 hour\n         = 10 miles\n\nTo find out how long it takes to cover the distance at a speed of 6 mph:\nTime = Distance / Speed\n     = 10 miles / 6 mph\n     ≈ 1.67 hours or about 1 hour and 40 minutes.\n\nSo, adding this to the initial 2 hours gives us the total time:\nTotal time = Initial time + Return time\n           = 2 hours + 1 hour 40 minutes\n           = 3 hours 40 minutes\n\nTherefore, it takes him approximately **3 hours 40 minutes** to get back home.'
