[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 7/100 path 7/8 answer="Let \\( G \\) represent the time it takes for Gerald to run the 400-meter hurdles before improving his diet. Since Lee was originally able to complete the race two seconds faster than Gerald, we have:\n\\[ L = G - 2 \\]\nwhere \\( L \\) represents Lee's original time. Given that Lee now takes 38 seconds, we substitute \\( L \\):\n\\[ 38 = G - 2 \\]\n\nSolving for \\( G \\), we get:\n\\[ G = 38 + 2 = 40 \\text{ seconds} \\]\n\nWith the improvement due to his diet, Gerald’s new running time will be 10% faster. Hence, we calculate 10% of \\( G \\):\n\n\\[ \\Delta t = 0.10 \\times G = 0.10 \\times 40 \\]\n\nSubstituting the value back into the equation gives us:\n\n\\[ G_{\\text{improved}} = G - \\Delta t = 40 - 4 = 36 \\text{ seconds} \\]\n\nThus, Gerald can now run the 400-meter hurdles at a speed equivalent to:\n\\[ \\boxed{36} \\] seconds."
