[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 15/100 path 3/8 answer="Let's break it down step by step:\n\n1. First, we calculate the total cost of the three tickets:\n   \\[3 \\text{ tickets} \\times \\$20.25 \\text{ per ticket} = \\$60.75\\]\n\n2. Since they spent $4.50 less on food than on the tickets, the cost of food can be calculated as follows:\n   \\[\\$60.75 (tickets) - \\$4.50 = \\$56.25\\]\n\n3. Now let's find out the total amount spent on rides. There were two rides at $33 each:\n   \\[2 \\text{ rides} \\times \\$33 \\text{ per ride} = \\$66\\]\n\n4. Adding up all these expenses gives us the total amount spent:\n   \\[\\$60.75 + \\$56.25 + \\$66 = \\$183\\]\n\n5. Finally, since they shared the total cost among themselves equally, we divide the total cost by the number of people sharing:\n   \\[$183 \\div 3 = \\$61\\]\n\nTherefore, each person paid $61."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 15/100 path 4/8 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 15/100 path 4/8 answer="Let's break it down step-by-step:\n\n1. **Tickets Cost**: \n   - Total cost of tickets is $20.25 (given).\n\n2. **Food Costs**:\n   - Food costs are $4.50 less than ticket costs.\n   - So, food cost = Ticket cost - $4.50\n   - Food cost = $20.25 - $4.50 = $15.75\n\n3. **Rides Costs**:\n   - Each ride costs $33.\n   - For two rides: total ride cost = $33 × 2 = $66.\n\nNow, let's calculate the total amount spent:\n\\[ \\text{Total cost} = \\text{Tickets cost} + \\text{Food cost} + \\text{Ride cost} \\]\n\\[ \\text{Total cost} = \\$20.25 + \\$15.75 + \\$66 \\]\n\nAdding these amounts together:\n\\[ \\text{Total cost} = \\$20.25 + \\$15.75 + \\$66 = \\$102 \\]\n\nNow, we need to divide the total cost by 3 because three friends are splitting the expenses equally:\n\\[ \\text{Cost per person} = \\frac{\\$102}{3} \\]\n\nCalculating the division:\n\\[ \\text{Cost per person} = \\$34 \\]\n\nSo, each friend paid $34."
