[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 30/100 path 4/8 answer="Let's denote the total number of steps Elliott walked as \\( T \\).\n\nElliott took half of his steps to and from school:\n\\[ \\frac{T}{2} \\]\n\nHe also took 1,000 steps for a short walk with his friend:\n\\[ 1000 \\text{ steps} \\]\n\nAfter these, he completed his jogging part:\n\\[ (T - \\frac{T}{2}) + 1000 = T - \\frac{T}{2} + 1000 \\]\nAfter finishing his jogging, he still had 2,000 steps left to take:\n\\[ T - \\frac{T}{2} + 1000 = 10000 - 2000 \\]\n\\[ T - \\frac{T}{2} + 1000 = 8000 \\]\nWe can simplify this equation:\n\\[ \\frac{T}{2} = 8000 - 1000 \\]\n\\[ \\frac{T}{2} = 7000 \\]\nMultiplying both sides by 2:\n\\[ T = 2 \\times 7000 \\]\n\\[ T = 14000 \\]\n\nSo, we have found out that Elliott took 14000 steps in total.\n\nTo find how many steps Elliott took during his jog, let’s subtract what he already did:\n\nSteps taken before jogging: \n\\[ \\frac{14000}{2} + 1000 \\]\n\\[ = 7000 + 1000 \\]\n\\[ = 8000 \\]\n\nTherefore, the steps taken during his jogging would be:\n\\[ 14000 - 8000 \\]\n\\[ = 6000 \\]\n\nThe answer is"
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 30/100 path 5/8 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 30/100 path 5/8 answer='Let S represent the number of steps taken while walking to and from school. So S/2 represents the number of steps taken while walking to and from school. Also let J represent the number of steps taken during his jog. We know that before his jog, Elliott had completed half his goal (10,000 steps), so we can write:\n\nS + 1000 + J = 10,000\n\nAfter his jog, he had 2,000 steps remaining, so we can write:\n\nS/2 + 1000 + J = 10,000 - 2,000\n\nWe now have two equations:\n1) S + 1000 + J = 10,000\n2) S/2 + 1000 + J = 8,000\n\nSubtract equation 2 from equation 1:\n(S + 1000 + J) - (S/2 + 1000 + J) = 10,000 - 8,000\nS - S/2 = 2,000\nMultiply both sides by 2:\n2S - S = 4,000\nS = 4,000\n\nElliott took 4,000 steps walking to and from school.\n\nNow substitute S back into one of our original equations:\n4,000 + 1000 + J = 10,000\n5,000 + J = 10,000\nJ = 10,000 - 5,000\nJ = 5,000\n\nElliott took 5,000 steps during his jog.\n\nThe answer'
