[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 77/100 path 7/8 answer="Let's denote the number of loaves Sam had last Friday as S. According to the problem, S = 70.\n\nThe bakery has 40 less than seven times as many loaves of bread as Sam had last Friday. So we can express this mathematically as:\n\nBakery loaves = 7S - 40\n\nNow substituting the value of S (which is 70) into the equation:\n\nBakery loaves = 7(70) - 40\nBakery loaves = 490 - 40\nBakery loaves = 450\n\nSo, the bakery has 450 loaves of bread."
