[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 78/100 path 4/8 answer='Let \\( S \\) represent the number of small stuffed animals sold, and \\( L \\) represent the number of large stuffed animals sold. \n\nWe know:\n\\[ S = 2L \\] (Teresa sold twice as many small stuffed animals as large ones)\n\nThe cost of each small stuffed animal is $4, so the total revenue from selling small stuffed animals is \\( 4S \\).\n\nThe cost of each large stuffed animal is \\( 3 \\times \\$4 = \\$12 \\), so the total revenue from selling large stuffed animals is \\( 12L \\).\n\nThe total earnings were $120, thus:\n\\[ 4S + 12L = 120 \\]\n\nSubstituting \\( S = 2L \\) into the equation gives us:\n\\[ 4(2L) + 12L = 120 \\]\n\\[ 8L + 12L = 120 \\]\n\\[ 20L = 120 \\]\n\nDividing both sides by 20 yields:\n\\[ L = 6 \\]\n\nTherefore, Teresa sold 6 large stuffed animals.\n\nSince \\( S = 2L \\):\n\\[ S = 2 \\times 6 = 12 \\]\n\nThus, Teresa sold 12 small stuffed animals today.'
