[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 path 1/8 answer='To find out how much it will cost to paint the room, we first need to calculate the total area of the walls that need to be painted. \n\nThe total area of the north wall (which is also the same as the south wall) is:\n\\[ \\text{Area}_{\\text{north}} = 10 \\times 8 = 80 \\text{ square feet} \\]\n\nThe total area of both the north and south walls together is:\n\\[ \\text{Total Area}_{\\text{north/south}} = 80 + 80 = 160 \\text{ square feet} \\]\n\nThe total area of the east wall is:\n\\[ \\text{Area}_{\\text{east}} = 5 \\times 8 = 40 \\text{ square feet} \\]\n\nThe total area of the west wall is:\n\\[ \\text{Area}_{\\text{west}} = 5 \\times 8 = 40 \\text{ square feet} \\]\n\nSo, the combined area of all four walls is:\n\\[ \\text{Total Area}_{\\text{all walls}} = 160 + 40 + 40 = 240 \\text{ square feet} \\]\n\nNow, since one gallon of paint covers 20 square feet, we can determine how many gallons are needed:\n\\[ \\text{Gallons Needed} = \\frac{\\text{Total Area}_{\\text{all walls}}}{\\text{Coverage per Gallon}} = \\frac{240}{20} = 12 \\text{ gallons} \\]\n\nFinally, multiplying the number of gallons by the cost per gallon gives us the total cost:\n\\[ \\text{Cost} = \\text{Gallons Needed} \\times \\text{Cost per Gallon} = 12 \\'
