[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 82/100 path 1/8 answer='Let \\( L \\) represent the number of large jellyfish initially present in the tank. According to the problem, these large jellyfish account for one-fifth of the total number of jellyfish:\n\\[ L = \\frac{1}{5} \\times T \\]\nwhere \\( T \\) represents the total number of jellyfish in the tank.\n\nA third of the large jellyfish change color when exposed to UV light, so:\n\\[ \\text{Number of large jellyfish turning blue} = \\frac{L}{3} \\]\n\nIt is also stated that there were 6 jellyfish that changed color. Therefore, we can set up the equation:\n\\[ \\frac{L}{3} = 6 \\]\n\nSolving for \\( L \\):\n\\[ L = 6 \\times 3 \\]\n\\[ L = 18 \\]\n\nNow substituting back into our initial equation for the total number of jellyfish (T), where \\( L = \\frac{1}{5} \\times T \\):\n\\[ 18 = \\frac{1}{5} \\times T \\]\n\\[ T = 18 \\times 5 \\]\n\\[ T = 90 \\]\n\nThus, the total number of jellyfish in the tank is:\n\\[ \\boxed{90} \\]'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 82/100 path 2/8 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 82/100 path 2/8 answer='Let \\( L \\) represent the number of large jellyfish, and let \\( S \\) represent the number of small jellyfish. According to the problem:\n\n\\[ \\frac{L}{5} = \\text{large jellyfish} \\]\n\\[ \\frac{\\text{large jellyfish}}{3} = \\text{jellyfish that change color} \\]\n\nGiven:\n\\[ \\frac{L}{5} + (\\text{large jellyfish}) = \\text{total jellyfish} \\]\n\\[ \\frac{L}{5} + \\frac{L}{15} = \\text{total jellyfish} \\]\n\nWe know that when the UV light was turned on, 6 jellyfish changed color, so:\n\\[ \\frac{L}{5} + \\frac{L}{15} = 6 \\]\n\nSolving for \\( L \\):\n\\[ \\frac{3L + L}{15} = 6 \\]\n\\[ 4L = 90 \\]\n\\[ L = 22.5 \\]\n\nSince the number of jellyfish must be whole, we assume \\( L \\) should round to 22 or 23. However, since the calculation suggests a fractional value, let’s recheck the interpretation assuming rounding errors.\n\nAssuming \\( L = 22 \\):\n\n\\[ \\frac{22}{5} + \\frac{22}{15} = 4.4 + 1.4667 = 5.8667 \\approx 6 \\]\n\nThus, with \\( L = 22 \\), the total count matches 6 jellyfish changing colors correctly.\n\nTherefore, the number of jellyfish in the tank is 22.'
